The nikto scan above provides us interesting information. Apparently the host is vulnerable to the shellshock vulnerability.

Exploitation


I used multi/http/apache_mod_cgi_bash_env_exec exploit inside Metasploit to gain a foothold on the machine. After setting the parameters, I launched the exploit.


The exploit worked and I gained a foothold!

Using the exploit from Metasploit above makes it too easy! Let's try to manually exploit this machine by using the shelllshock payload.


The bottom terminal on the picture above exploits the shellshock vulnerability. This creates a reverse shell connection back to my listener on port 8443.

Privilege Escalation


Running uname -a shows this kernel is vulnerable to the Dirty Cowexploit! And the target host has gcc installed so we can compile the exploit.


I transferred this exploit to the target machine. After running the exploit, it was successful because the new user firefart was added.


Now I have a root shell by switching to the new user created by the exploit.
